                <h1>ARMS AND ARMORY</h1>
                <p>Arms and armours of Indian rulers as well as British officials are one of the most popular sections
                    of the Victoria Memorial Hall. Lord Curzon had desired to acquire arms and armour from the rulers of
                    the different princely states of India. Swords, spears, shields, decorative daggers, guns etc are on
                    display at the museum. The museum has a rich collection of antique matchlock, flintlock and
                    percussion guns of Indian, Turkish and European origin. Rifles used during the First World War are
                    currently on display in the Prince Hall. Their form, shape, design and ornamentations are
                    fascinating.</p>
