                    <h1>INDIAN PAINTINGS</h1>
                    <p>Victoria Memorial Hall showcases an outstanding array of artworks by Indian artists spanning the ages. From the intricate strokes of Mughal miniature paintings and Rajput traditions to the vibrant expressions of modern Indian art, the museum’s collection is a testament to the rich cultural heritage of the subcontinent.

                        Among the esteemed artists featured are Nandalal Bose, Abanindranath Tagore, Gaganendranath Tagore, Asit Halder, Benod Behari Mukherjee, Mukul Dey, Jamini Roy, Sunayani Devi, and many others. Their works reflect a diverse range of styles, techniques and themes, capturing the essence of India’s artistic evolution over the centuries.
